		<title type="html"><![CDATA[ARIA in HTML is a W3C Recommendation]]></title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.w3.org/blog/news/archives/9367" />

		<id>https://www.w3.org/blog/news/?p=9367</id>
		<updated>2021-12-09T08:46:24Z</updated>
		<published>2021-12-09T08:46:24Z</published>
		<category scheme="https://www.w3.org/blog/news" term="Home Page Stories" /><category scheme="https://www.w3.org/blog/news" term="Publication" /><category scheme="https://www.w3.org/blog/news" term="Web Design and Applications" />
		<summary type="html"><![CDATA[The Web Applications Working Group has published ARIA in HTML as a W3C Recommendation. This specification defines the authoring rules (author conformance requirements) for the use of Accessible Rich Internet Applications (WAI-ARIA) 1.1 and Digital Publishing WAI-ARIA Module 1.0 attributes on [HTML] elements. This specification&#8217;s primary objective is to define requirements for use with conformance [&#8230;]]]></summary>

					<content type="html" xml:base="https://www.w3.org/blog/news/archives/9367"><![CDATA[<p>The <a href="https://www.w3.org/groups/wg/webapps">Web Applications Working Group</a> has published <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/2021/REC-html-aria-20211209/">ARIA in HTML</a> as a W3C Recommendation. This specification defines the authoring rules (author conformance requirements) for the use of <cite><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/">Accessible Rich Internet Applications (WAI-ARIA) 1.1</a></cite> and <cite><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/dpub-aria-1.0/">Digital Publishing WAI-ARIA Module 1.0</a></cite> attributes on [<a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/2021/REC-html-aria-20211209/#bib-html">HTML</a>] elements. This specification&#8217;s primary objective is to define requirements for use with conformance checking tools used by authors (i.e., web developers). These requirements will aid authors in their development of web content, including custom interfaces/widgets, that makes use of ARIA to complement or extend the features of the host language [<a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/2021/REC-html-aria-20211209/#bib-html">HTML</a>].</p>
]]></content>
		
